<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1762,1931]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,1763,1787]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Remarks.</emphasis>
Paler than 
<emphasis box="[439,603,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">P. b u r m i n d i c u s</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[661,779,1763,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rameshi">
<emphasis box="[661,779,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">P. rameshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below), lacking facial spots and costal brown stripe. 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant" box="[197,537,1798,1822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" refString="Distant, W. L (1908) Rhynchota. Homoptera and Appendix (Pt.). In: Bingham, C. T. (ed) The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Volume IV, xv + 501 pp. Taylor &amp; Francis, London." type="book" year="1908">
Distant (
<number box="[296,357,1798,1822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" value="1908.0">1908</number>
: 
<number box="[371,416,1798,1822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" value="347.0">347</number>
, Fig. 
<number box="[485,529,1798,1822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" value="220.0">220</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
translated and reproduced the description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Melichar" box="[1071,1257,1798,1822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" refString="Melichar, L. (1903) Fauna von Ceylon. iv + 248. Verlag von Felix L. Dames, Berlin." type="book chapter" year="1903">
Melichar (
<number box="[1191,1249,1798,1822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" value="1903.0">1903</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
in English and placed this species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fieber. However" authorityName="Fieber. However" box="[517,823,1834,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Phlepsius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[517,626,1835,1859]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Phlepsius</emphasis>
Fieber. However
</taxonomicName>
, it is clear that Distant misidentified the species as he figured a different species (
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang" box="[456,697,1870,1894]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" refString="Zhang, Y., M. D. Webb (1996) A revised classification of the Asian and Pacific Selenocephalinae leafhoppers (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, entomology Series, 65, 1 - 103." type="journal article" year="1996">
Zhang &amp; Webb 
<number box="[637,697,1870,1894]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1762,1931]" box="[197,1368,1906,1931]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
This is the only species of 
<taxonomicName box="[495,618,1907,1931]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[495,618,1907,1931]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Parallygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possessing a sclerotized bridge across the pygofer lobes (
<figureCitation box="[1265,1333,1906,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1598,1621]" captionTargetBox="[237,1357,228,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[191,1395,193,1577]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Parallygus divaricatus Melichar. A. Male genital capsule; B. Pygofer process, ventral view; C. Connective, anteroventral view; D. Sclerotized bridge across pygofer lobes, posterior view; E. Style and connective, posterodorsal view; F. Aedeagus, lateral view. Free hand diagrams not to scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210587/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
Fig. 
<number box="[1317,1333,1906,1930]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D).
</paragraph>
